---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="End-to-end Lifecycle Automation">
  <h1>End-to-end lifecycle automation</h1>
  <p>
    Zoom out from any one beat and this is the whole loop, running automatically on every future
    change to this repo:
  </p>
  <pre>Issue → Copilot drafts PR → Copilot Code Review → Agent Merge →
GitHub Actions (build + supply-chain security + deploy) → GitHub Pages</pre>
  <p>
    You set this up once, on this repo, in an afternoon. From then on, every feature request,
    every dependency bump, every content change moves through the same reviewed, secured,
    deployed path — with no step depending on someone remembering to do it.
  </p>
  <p>
    That's the payoff of "shipping with AI": not that AI writes the code, but that the whole
    pipeline around the code keeps itself healthy.
  </p>
</Layout>
